WEBVTT

00:26.944 --> 00:30.364
Caitlyn,
this is a process, okay?

00:30.364 --> 00:32.491
But it's important
for you to remember

00:32.491 --> 00:37.079
that the only person
who can save us is ourselves.

00:37.079 --> 00:38.789
He's a monster.

00:38.789 --> 00:40.832
A goddamn fucking monster.

00:40.832 --> 00:42.751
That's what he is.

00:44.544 --> 00:46.630
But I can't seem
to get away from him.

00:46.630 --> 00:50.008
Do you remember what drew you
to Mitch in the first place?

00:50.008 --> 00:52.261
We met at work, and...

00:55.013 --> 00:59.476
...he was charming
and mysterious.

01:00.727 --> 01:04.815
He wined and dined me
and took me traveling,

01:04.815 --> 01:06.400
and...

01:06.400 --> 01:09.611
he told me it was me and him
against the world.

01:11.280 --> 01:14.032
He made me feel important.

01:14.032 --> 01:15.450
Hello.

01:15.450 --> 01:17.995
My name is
Robert Montague Renfield.

01:17.995 --> 01:20.247
And just like
all these decent folks,

01:20.247 --> 01:23.083
I am in
a destructive relationship.

01:30.632 --> 01:32.926
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
That was a lot.

01:32.926 --> 01:35.929
Maybe we should just back up
to the beginning.

01:37.431 --> 01:42.936
Mr. Renfield, I bid you welcome.

01:42.936 --> 01:45.188
I am...

01:45.188 --> 01:46.773
-Dracula.

01:46.773 --> 01:48.775
When I met him,
I was a real estate lawyer

01:48.775 --> 01:51.320
hoping to make a deal
that would change my life

01:51.320 --> 01:53.196
and my family's lives forever.

01:53.196 --> 01:54.698
Oh, and it most certainly did.

01:54.698 --> 01:59.786
You will make a very good
assistant, Mr. Renfield.

01:59.786 --> 02:02.372
I understand how Caitlyn feels.

02:02.372 --> 02:04.666
I never drink wine.

02:04.666 --> 02:06.501
He also wined and dined me.

02:06.501 --> 02:08.170
He made me feel important.

02:08.170 --> 02:12.007
He introduced me
into high society.

02:12.007 --> 02:13.800
-We went to the theater.

02:14.760 --> 02:18.305
-We traveled to exotic places.

02:18.305 --> 02:20.640
And then he made me
his familiar.

02:21.975 --> 02:25.228
Which means that I take care
of Master's every need.

02:26.063 --> 02:27.647
Including staff changes

02:27.647 --> 02:30.150
and arranging his special
dietary requirements.

02:31.860 --> 02:35.405
Look, I didn't just jump into
serving the Prince of Darkness.

02:35.405 --> 02:36.823
We had some great times.

02:37.866 --> 02:39.326
But just like all great times...

02:39.326 --> 02:41.661
-Servant.
-...they come to an end.

02:41.661 --> 02:44.539
The hunters have returned.

02:45.374 --> 02:46.500
Ah, yes.

02:46.500 --> 02:48.335
The bugs. This comes up a lot.

02:48.335 --> 02:51.505
Dracula's powers come from
consuming human life.

02:51.505 --> 02:53.298
Mine come from eating bugs.

02:53.298 --> 02:56.176
Make sense? Great.
Now, where were we?

03:06.186 --> 03:08.814
-I'm coming, Master!

03:08.814 --> 03:10.273
Shit. Fuck. Shit.

03:11.191 --> 03:12.609
Shit. Fuck. Shit. Fuck.

03:19.866 --> 03:22.702
Sh-Sh-Sh-Shit.

03:25.038 --> 03:27.207
This is a protection circle,
Renfield.

03:27.207 --> 03:29.084
Mm.

03:29.084 --> 03:30.377
He cannot escape.

03:30.377 --> 03:32.963
Let us rid this world
of his evil,

03:32.963 --> 03:34.464
and you can finally be free!

03:34.464 --> 03:37.008
Free?

03:37.008 --> 03:40.804
The moment I'm gone,

03:40.804 --> 03:44.516
they will lock you away
for what you've done for me.

03:45.559 --> 03:49.312
I am your only salvation.

03:52.566 --> 03:56.903
I am your only friend.

03:58.989 --> 04:03.243
I am the only one

04:03.243 --> 04:05.662
who cares for you.

04:05.662 --> 04:08.373
I actually remember thinking,

04:08.373 --> 04:11.418
"He really, really means it
this time."

04:16.298 --> 04:18.091
Renfield!

04:18.091 --> 04:20.677
We are the last of our kind.

04:20.677 --> 04:24.347
From now on, every drop of blood
Dracula spills

04:24.347 --> 04:26.433
will be on your hands.

04:32.439 --> 04:35.942
Fuck. I was not expecting that.

04:42.282 --> 04:44.284
Or that.

04:59.508 --> 05:03.220
Master, you okay?

05:03.220 --> 05:04.930
No.

05:05.889 --> 05:08.016
Yeah.

05:08.016 --> 05:09.976
This is a fairly typical result.

05:09.976 --> 05:12.312
At the peak of his powers,
Dracula goes on

05:12.312 --> 05:14.356
a full-tilt
blood-sucking bender,

05:14.356 --> 05:16.983
the good guys show up
and do their thing,

05:16.983 --> 05:19.694
and then it's up to me
to clean up the mess.

05:19.694 --> 05:23.240
- -It's what
I call our transitional period.

05:23.240 --> 05:26.910
So I take him to a new city,
nurse him back to full power,

05:26.910 --> 05:29.079
find a decent place
to ride it out

05:29.079 --> 05:32.290
until the whole cycle starts
all over again.

05:32.290 --> 05:34.000
Uh, excuse me. H-Hi.

05:34.000 --> 05:35.627
May I borrow a pen, please?

05:37.295 --> 05:38.713
Thank... you.

05:41.132 --> 05:43.260
Which brings us back here.

05:43.260 --> 05:46.680
In the meantime, I come here
and listen to these poor souls

05:46.680 --> 05:49.057
talk about their monsters.

05:49.057 --> 05:50.850
You were just talking
about Mitch, what...

05:50.850 --> 05:54.354
I know this is, like,
way down the list of bad stuff,

05:54.354 --> 05:57.023
but he's also really into ska.

05:57.023 --> 05:59.484
-The kind of music?
-Yes.

05:59.484 --> 06:02.696
Fishbone, Mustard Plug,
Voodoo Glow Skulls.

06:02.696 --> 06:04.614
I fucking hate that shit!

06:06.575 --> 06:08.076
I'm so sorry, Caitlyn. I'm so...

06:08.076 --> 06:10.662
-Mark, I am... I'm so sorry.
-It's okay.

06:10.662 --> 06:13.373
Is that the one
that's 99% horns?

06:13.373 --> 06:14.666
Yeah, see,
that's what I was thinking.

06:14.666 --> 06:16.793
