And before he passed,
I promised your father that

18:03.958 --> 18:05.668
I would do my best
to take care of you.

18:05.668 --> 18:08.921
But sometimes, you got to know
when to play ball.

18:08.921 --> 18:11.215
This ain't your stepping stone.

18:11.215 --> 18:12.800
It's your rock bottom.

18:21.600 --> 18:24.437
What the fuck are you guys
looking at, huh?

18:37.992 --> 18:39.493
Shit.

18:41.329 --> 18:43.372
What'd you do this time?

18:45.249 --> 18:47.126
What I do every time.

18:47.126 --> 18:49.128
Catch Teddy Lobo
committing a crime, and then:

18:49.128 --> 18:51.714
What? Oh, surprise,
he got away with it again.

18:51.714 --> 18:54.633
And what about your-your little
FBI, uh, task force up there?

18:54.633 --> 18:56.302
You guys been back
for four months.

18:56.302 --> 18:58.095
What have you done
about the Lobos?

18:58.095 --> 18:59.972
Oh, oh, oh, a-a wiretap?

18:59.972 --> 19:01.390
Subpoena?
A fucking parking ticket?

19:01.390 --> 19:04.018
A hard stare across a diner?

19:04.018 --> 19:07.313
I am just as mad about
what they did to Dad as you are.

19:07.313 --> 19:09.857
I want revenge
just as bad as you do.

19:09.857 --> 19:12.485
But every day, I force myself
to swallow that anger

19:12.485 --> 19:14.820
so I don't fuck up
my investigation.

19:14.820 --> 19:18.157
And if you cannot learn
to let that go...

19:19.325 --> 19:21.535
...you're never gonna get
the justice that you want.

19:24.497 --> 19:27.458
You're not the only one
who lost a dad here.

19:34.840 --> 19:36.008
♪ Murder, murder, murder ♪

19:36.008 --> 19:37.176
♪ When he bust in ♪

19:37.176 --> 19:38.260
♪ Murder, murder, murder ♪

19:38.260 --> 19:39.512
♪ When he bust in... ♪

19:39.512 --> 19:41.347
Here you go.
Take care of yourself.

19:41.347 --> 19:42.515
-You earned it. Shower yourself
in it. -(gasps) Thanks.

19:42.515 --> 19:44.350
-Teddy.
-Ooh! Okay.

19:44.350 --> 19:46.352
Your mother wants to see you.

19:46.352 --> 19:47.686
All right.

19:47.686 --> 19:49.522
♪ Murder, murder, murder,
when he bust in ♪

19:49.522 --> 19:50.940
♪ Murder, murder, murder... ♪

19:50.940 --> 19:52.817
Downstairs.

19:52.817 --> 19:55.194
♪ You might've heard of him,
the guy lost his nerve. ♪

19:56.695 --> 19:59.740
Long, even strokes.

19:59.740 --> 20:01.492
Hey, Mom.

20:02.952 --> 20:04.495
Teddy.

20:04.495 --> 20:06.455
You said you want...
You said you wanted to see me?

20:06.455 --> 20:08.916
Take a seat, please.

20:14.422 --> 20:18.217
Do you even know why we became

20:18.217 --> 20:22.263
the most powerful crime family
in this city?

20:22.263 --> 20:25.224
We're not the biggest.
We're not the richest.

20:25.224 --> 20:29.728
However, we are the most feared.

20:29.728 --> 20:33.315
Our reputation for
ruthlessness and violence

20:33.315 --> 20:36.902
is something I have worked
very hard to cultivate.

20:36.902 --> 20:39.905
But lately,
our enemies don't seem to be

20:39.905 --> 20:41.532
as afraid as they used to be.

20:41.532 --> 20:43.742
They're fucking scared, Mom.

20:43.742 --> 20:48.289
Not the two-bit punks
stealing our drugs.

20:49.081 --> 20:51.584
Not the five families.

20:52.460 --> 20:55.629
And not
that fucking traffic cop.

20:55.629 --> 20:59.341
This family is an empire, Teddy.

20:59.341 --> 21:04.263
I built an empire.

21:05.389 --> 21:08.309
And I need to know
its future is secure.

21:11.520 --> 21:14.857
I need to know
whose hands it belongs in.

21:14.857 --> 21:20.279
And I need to know those hands
can get a little dirty.

21:20.279 --> 21:22.656
I know Teddy's up to something.

21:23.949 --> 21:26.619
I'm gonna find the evidence
to make it stick.

21:26.619 --> 21:29.038
Got a lot of orange paint.

21:32.833 --> 21:35.628
What is that?
Some kind of warning?

21:37.630 --> 21:39.715
I think it's lyrics
to a ska song.

21:41.175 --> 21:43.636
Ska's not dead.

21:43.636 --> 21:45.054
Fuck.

21:54.355 --> 21:56.315
♪ You can touch the sky ♪

21:56.315 --> 21:58.984
-♪ 'Cause there's a shot ♪

21:58.984 --> 22:00.819
♪ In the night ♪

22:00.819 --> 22:02.780
♪ Turning darkness
into light... ♪

22:02.780 --> 22:05.074
Oh, you've got to be kidding me.

22:10.287 --> 22:12.456
Yeah! All right!

22:16.669 --> 22:19.046
You think
you'll get answers here?

22:20.381 --> 22:22.132
I think we'll get dinner.

22:22.132 --> 22:24.343
Maybe answers for dessert.

22:25.135 --> 22:26.512
There she is.

22:26.512 --> 22:28.514
You sure you want
to do this, Teddy?

22:28.514 --> 22:30.558
Yes, I am sure
I want to do this.

22:30.558 --> 22:32.643
That cop needs to be reminded
who runs this town.

22:56.875 --> 22:58.502
Oh, shit.

22:59.211 --> 23:00.421
Fuck.

23:00.421 --> 23:02.506
Oh, this is not a good look.

23:02.506 --> 23:04.216
Not a good look at all.
Abort. Abort.

23:04.216 --> 23:06.051
Can you order me a number three?

23:06.051 --> 23:08.596
The toilet just ordered
a number two.

23:17.313 --> 23:19.690
Sorry.

23:24.987 --> 23:27.323
Who the fuck are these guys?

23:38.375 --> 23:41.462
Move, and I'll blow
your fucking head off.

23:42.963 --> 23:44.715
-Take that, tourist!

23:47.343 --> 23:49.094
Get down!

23:50.095 --> 23:51.430
Hey, do me a favor.

23:51.430 --> 23:53.682
Just remain calm,

23:53.682 --> 23:58.062
and almost nobody will get hurt.

23:58.062 --> 23:59.480
Thank you, Teddy.

23:59.480 --> 24:01.273
I came here to connect you
to a crime scene,

24:01.273 --> 24:02.858
and you go and turn it into one.

24:06.195 --> 24:08.072
What you trying to do?

24:08.072 --> 24:10.616
Holy shit, were you trying
to imitate your dad?

24:10.616 --> 24:14.453
What do you think,
your dad died some brave hero?

24:14.453 --> 24:16.622
We beat the shit
out of your father.

24:16.622 --> 24:19.458
And while he was lying there
on the floor,

24:19.458 --> 24:21.502
he begged for his life.

24:21.502 --> 24:23.337
Your dad was a coward.

24:23.337 --> 24:26.465
But you know what? I want to
save you that embarrassment.

24:26.465 --> 24:29.009
I'm gonna give you
the chance to live.

24:30.135 --> 24:34.056
All you have to do
is admit to everybody here

24:34.056 --> 24:36.600
that we own you, too.

24:36.600 --> 24:38.185
So, what's it gonna be?

24:38.185 --> 24:39.186
Shoot me.

24:39.186 --> 24:40.312
What?

24:40.312 --> 24:41.814
You heard me, asshole.

24:41.814 --> 24:42.856
Shoot me.

24:42.856 --> 24:44.983
Shoot me like you shot my dad.

24:44.983 --> 24:47.277
Or was that not you?

24:47.277 --> 24:48.654
Were you waiting in the car

24:48.654 --> 24:50.656
while one of your boys
did it for you?

24:52.032 --> 24:53.492
I'm more than happy
to do it, Teddy.

24:53.492 --> 24:54.868
Shut the fuck up.

24:55.703 --> 24:57.913
Have you ever shot
someone before?

24:57.913 --> 24:59.748
I've shot
a million fucking people.

24:59.748 --> 25:01.583
Then add me to the list.

25:01.583 --> 25:03.001
Come on, tough guy. Shoot me.

25:03.001 --> 25:04.628
If you think
this is a fucking game,

25:04.628 --> 25:06.213
I will shoot you
in your fucking face.

25:06.213 --> 25:08.674
-Yeah? Dare you.

25:10.676 --> 25:14.012
You want to be
a fucking hero right now?

25:14.012 --> 25:15.556
Okay, fine.

25:15.556 --> 25:17.683
Here we go.

25:18.475 --> 25:20.060
Congratulations.

25:22.771 --> 25:24.565
You're better than your father.

26:27.336 --> 26:29.254
Fuck! Shit!

26:51.276 --> 26:52.903
-Oh.

26:55.948 --> 26:57.324
Are you okay?

26:57.324 --> 26:58.575
Yeah. Yeah. Oh...

26:58.575 --> 27:00.160
That was amazing.
You were amazing.

27:00.160 --> 27:01.787
What you did.

27:01.787 --> 27:03.914
You stood up to him.

27:04.790 --> 27:06.583
How did you do that?

27:06.583 --> 27:07.918
What kind of life would I lead

27:07.918 --> 27:09.628
under the thumb
of one of those assholes?

27:09.628 --> 27:13.215
A very... a very sad one.

27:13.215 --> 27:14.466
Yeah.

27:14.466 --> 27:16.134
Did I watch you
cut a guy's arms off

27:16.134 --> 27:17.636
with a decorative
serving platter?

27:17.636 --> 27:20.180
Oh, uh, y-yeah.

27:20.180 --> 27:21.431
That was adrenaline.

27:21.431 --> 27:23.642
Uh, it was awesome.

27:25.853 --> 27:27.980
Um, I-I'm-I'm Rebecca Quincy.

27:27.980 --> 27:29.606
Officer... Officer Quincy.

27:29.606 --> 27:32.442
Robert Montague Renfield.

27:32.442 --> 27:34.611
Oh, uh, Montague. Cool.

27:34.611 --> 27:36.321
Are you from around here or...

27:36.321 --> 27:38.490
Oh, no. I'm...

27:38.490 --> 27:40.325
Uh, everywhere.

27:40.325 --> 27:41.910
Ah, military.

27:41.910 --> 27:44.204
That-that would explain
all the moves.

27:44.204 --> 27:47.708
Yeah, but forever ago--
the Great War.

27:47.708 --> 27:49.918
Uh... Iraq.

27:49.918 --> 27:51.336
Maybe not great, uh, you know,

27:51.336 --> 27:53.463
but overall pretty good--
three out of five stars.

27:53.463 --> 27:54.840
I'm sorry.

27:54.840 --> 27:58.677
I don't mean to interrupt
whatever this is,

27:58.677 --> 28:00.470
but...

28:00.470 --> 28:02.431
can we get up now?

28:02.431 --> 28:04.182
Uh, yeah.

28:04.182 --> 28:06.059
If I could have everyone
please, uh,

28:06.059 --> 28:08.145
just line up for me
for witness statements.

28:08.145 --> 28:10.647
And if we could all thank
Mr. Renfield

28:10.647 --> 28:13.650
for his brave, uh,
efforts today.

28:13.650 --> 28:15.277
Thank you, Mr. Renfield.

28:15.277 --> 28:17.195
You are the man, Mr. Renfield.

28:17.195 --> 28:19.323
And, um, thank you.

28:20.032 --> 28:22.409
Y-You... you saved my life.

28:22.409 --> 28:24.703
I...

28:24.703 --> 28:26.914
saved a life?

28:27.789 --> 28:29.833
You saved all our lives.

28:31.960 --> 28:33.545
You must really not be
from around here,

28:33.545 --> 28:36.673
'cause we certainly don't see
your kind very often.

28:36.673 --> 28:38.592
I'm sorry, what kind is that?

28:38.592 --> 28:40.844
Heroes.

28:44.556 --> 28:46.391
Hmm.

28:49.811 --> 28:52.898
Wow. That was amazing.

28:52.898 --> 28:55.901
She is amazing.

28:56.735 --> 28:58.236
And she saw me.

28:58.236 --> 29:00.697
She really saw me.

29:00.697 --> 29:03.283
That hasn't happened in ages.

29:03.283 --> 29:05.327
I'd forgotten
what it feels like.

29:05.327 --> 29:07.454
-Maybe there is hope.
-Oh, God bless you.

29:07.454 --> 29:08.747
Maybe she can...

29:08.747 --> 29:10.457
Renfield.

29:10.457 --> 29:13.669
What are you doing?

29:13.669 --> 29:16.088
Get here now.

29:16.088 --> 29:17.923
Ah, fuck.

29:17.923 --> 29:20.050
Do you think it's too late
to grab one of those nuns?

29:22.928 --> 29:26.139
What did we talk about
yesterday?

29:26.139 --> 29:27.265
U-Um...

29:27.265 --> 29:30.936
I've been up all day
thinking about it.

29:30.936 --> 29:33.563
Oh. What's this?

29:33.563 --> 29:36.024
Ah. My plan.

29:36.024 --> 29:37.609
Your plan?

29:37.609 --> 29:40.570
But your plan has always been
to just drink blood.

29:40.570 --> 29:42.030
Exactly.

29:42.030 --> 29:44.533
What have I been doing
all these years?

29:44.533 --> 29:47.953
I mean, look at me,
lurking in the shadows and filth

29:47.953 --> 29:50.038
like some kind
of a diseased animal.

29:50.038 --> 29:52.082
You said it yourself--
I deserve better.

29:52.082 --> 29:57.504
So, why am I not embracing
what I truly am?

29:58.505 --> 29:59.798
Which is?

30:00.590 --> 30:04.011
A god, Renfield.

30:04.011 --> 30:07.806
An immortal, insatiable--

30:07.806 --> 30:11.393
whoo!-- all-powerful being.

30:11.393 --> 30:14.312
Everything you said about
the modern world is true.

30:14.312 --> 30:18.233
-It is a dangerous place.
-Hmm.

30:18.233 --> 30:20.485
Only not for us.

30:20.485 --> 30:25.198
For them, it's a dangerous,
sad, broken place

30:25.198 --> 30:27.701
full of fear and desperation.

30:27.701 --> 30:29.202
It's weak.

30:29.202 --> 30:32.748
Longing for a powerful force
to guide it,

30:32.748 --> 30:37.711
control it, dominate it.

30:37.711 --> 30:39.546
-Like you.
-Hmm.

30:39.546 --> 30:44.009
I mean, this entire society
was designed by Renfields,

30:44.009 --> 30:45.844
for Renfields.

30:45.844 --> 30:49.806
So, why should I
have to adapt to it?

30:49.806 --> 30:52.893
It should have to adapt to me.

30:54.227 --> 30:56.354
-I owe it all to you, servant.
-Oh, no.

30:56.354 --> 30:58.231
I think you actually might have
read between the lines

30:58.231 --> 30:59.691
-a little bit there.
-Indeed.

30:59.691 --> 31:01.818
We're in this together,

31:01.818 --> 31:03.945
Dracula and Renfield.

31:05.030 --> 31:07.574
From now on, humanity
will no longer be divided

31:07.574 --> 31:10.035
by the good and the evil,

31:10.035 --> 31:14.206
only by followers...

31:14.206 --> 31:16.625
and food.

31:20.253 --> 31:24.800
You and I forever,
until the end of time.

31:24.800 --> 31:26.927
Bloody hell.

31:27.886 --> 31:30.388
How is my life?

31:30.388 --> 31:32.557
My life is like a...

31:32.557 --> 31:37.104
never-ending hallway
of fun house mirrors, but...

31:37.104 --> 31:39.397
all the clowns are me.

31:39.397 --> 31:40.899
Uh, hey, everyone.

31:40.899 --> 31:42.901
I need your help.

31:42.901 --> 31:44.069
Are you okay?

31:44.069 --> 31:45.904
No.

31:47.072 --> 31:49.741
I need to get out
of a toxic relationship.

31:49.741 --> 31:53.662
Okay. Well, well, well, well,
take a seat and let her rip.

31:53.662 --> 31:55.247
Okay, thanks.

31:55.247 --> 31:57.249
Okay, yeah. Fuck Carol, I guess.

31:57.249 --> 31:58.708
It's...

31:58.708 --> 32:00.252
I hate her, too.

32:00.252 --> 32:02.170
Why don't you start
by telling us

32:02.170 --> 32:04.089
what brought you here
in the first place.

32:04.089 --> 32:06.007
I was on the job.

32:06.007 --> 32:07.634
Uh, for my boss.

32:07.634 --> 32:09.845
Uh, well, and I was
actually following Bob,

32:09.845 --> 32:11.888
because I thought
that Bob would make

32:11.888 --> 32:13.932
a very good, um, uh...

32:15.517 --> 32:17.018
Friend?

32:17.853 --> 32:19.729
Yes. Thank you, Bob.

32:19.729 --> 32:20.981
Thank you, Renfield.

32:20.981 --> 32:23.650
And then, you know,
I started to hear

32:23.650 --> 32:27.529
all of your stories and...

32:31.158 --> 32:34.286
I mean, they were all so sad.

32:35.620 --> 32:37.247
That's us.

32:37.247 --> 32:42.169
And, you know,
for the first time in years,

32:42.169 --> 32:44.171
I felt like I wasn't alone.

32:45.130 --> 32:47.382
-You realized you're
a codependent. -Mm-hmm.

32:47.382 --> 32:49.634
I need to change. I can see
that I-I need to change,

32:49.634 --> 32:52.304
and, uh, I want to, but my boss,

32:52.304 --> 32:54.055
he's pretty delusional, I think.

32:54.055 --> 32:56.683
Uh, he thinks
he can take over the world.

32:56.683 --> 32:59.269
-He's a narcissist, Renfield.

32:59.269 --> 33:00.645
We all know exactly
how you feel.

33:00.645 --> 33:01.771
-Yes.
-Exactly.

33:01.771 --> 33:03.356
No, he's different.

33:03.356 --> 33:05.358
-You can't get him
out of your head. -No.

33:05.358 --> 33:06.860
Ooh, and you feel like
he could kill you

33:06.860 --> 33:08.236
with the snap of his fingers.

33:08.236 --> 33:10.113
-Yes. Wouldn't even
need to snap. -Oh.

33:10.113 --> 33:12.657
He controls rats with his mind.

33:12.657 --> 33:14.034
Uh...

33:14.034 --> 33:15.202
It's okay, it's okay.
He's on medication.

33:15.202 --> 33:19.247
Renfield, this is
codependency 101.

33:19.247 --> 33:21.249
A narcissist will take
full advantage

33:21.249 --> 33:23.293
of a codependent's
low self-esteem,

33:23.293 --> 33:27.839
but you're the one
with the real power.

33:27.839 --> 33:31.176
And all you got to do
is take it back.

33:31.176 --> 33:32.677
How do I do that?

33:32.677 --> 33:35.263
Focus on your needs.

33:35.263 --> 33:38.141
I mean, I just haven't
thought about

33:38.141 --> 33:39.935
any of my needs in years.

33:39.935 --> 33:42.812
But if you were to stop focusing
on his needs, what would happen?

33:42.812 --> 33:44.856
If I don't...

33:44.856 --> 33:45.857
Yeah, what would happen?

33:45.857 --> 33:47.067
Stop focusing on his needs.

33:47.067 --> 33:48.652
What would happen?

33:48.652 --> 33:50.320
-He won't grow to full power.

33:50.320 --> 33:52.697
Exactly.
He won't grow to full power.

33:52.697 --> 33:54.241
What? That's so weird.

33:54.241 --> 33:56.034
Why would you phrase it
like that?

33:56.034 --> 33:58.119
But yes, he's right.

33:58.119 --> 33:59.829
He's absolutely right.

33:59.829 --> 34:01.581
He won't grow to full power.

34:01.581 --> 34:04.417
You can take all that energy
you've spent on him

34:04.417 --> 34:06.336
and put it toward yourself.

34:06.336 --> 34:11.758
And then you will be the one
who grows to full power.

34:11.758 --> 34:13.260
-Yes.
-Full power.

34:13.260 --> 34:14.970
Me grow...
I-I'm gonna grow to full power?

34:14.970 --> 34:16.972
I want to hear you say it.

34:16.972 --> 34:19.140
Say, "I'm gonna grow
to full power."

34:19.140 --> 34:21.226
I-I-I'm gonna grow
to full power.

34:21.226 --> 34:23.645
I heard you say it,
but I didn't believe you.

34:23.645 --> 34:25.605
-Nope.
-Let me hear you say it again.

34:25.605 --> 34:27.732
-I'm gonna grow to full power.
-Yes!

34:27.732 --> 34:29.567
I see a smile there
because you like it.

34:29.567 --> 34:31.903
Now, say it like
the world needs to hear it.

34:31.903 --> 34:34.572
I'm gonna grow to full power.

34:34.572 --> 34:35.490
There you go!

34:37.117 --> 34:38.702
-Yes!
-That guy who walks

34:38.702 --> 34:41.413
in here every single week,
say goodbye to him.

34:41.413 --> 34:44.749
This is the person you are now.

34:44.749 --> 34:47.043
♪ Oh, oh, oh, am I ready? ♪

34:47.043 --> 34:48.920
♪ Girl, there ain't a doubt ♪

34:48.920 --> 34:50.505
♪ Am I ready? ♪

34:50.505 --> 34:53.300
-♪ What you talkin' 'bout? ♪
-♪ Am I ready? ♪

34:53.300 --> 34:55.093
♪ You gon' figure it out ♪

34:55.093 --> 34:58.513
♪ To be loved, to be loved ♪

34:58.513 --> 35:02.100
♪ You found me,
I was fed up with the fantasy ♪

35:02.100 --> 35:03.893
♪ What you wanna do... ♪

35:03.893 --> 35:05.228
Here you go.

35:05.228 --> 35:07.063
The power is in your hands.

35:07.063 --> 35:08.315
That book is your armor.

35:08.315 --> 35:10.275
It's your weapon.
It's your Bible.

35:10.275 --> 35:13.153
That's a cool ant farm.

35:13.153 --> 35:14.195
Is there room for one more?

35:14.195 --> 35:16.364
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

35:17.532 --> 35:18.950
Thank you.

35:20.577 --> 35:22.287
Let's give him some ideas.

35:22.287 --> 35:23.913
Do you know what a brush is?

35:23.913 --> 35:25.707
-♪ Am I ready? ♪
-♪ Girl, there ain't a doubt ♪

35:25.707 --> 35:27.625
Oh, and clean
them nasty fingernails.

35:27.625 --> 35:29.961
-♪ What you talkin' 'bout? ♪
-♪ Am I ready? ♪

35:29.961 --> 35:31.963
Spa day. I'll go with you.

35:31.963 --> 35:33.423
♪ To be loved... ♪

35:33.423 --> 35:35.133
Get your chakras
balanced, homes.

35:35.133 --> 35:37.552
Ooh, and update
that wardrobe to this century.

35:37.552 --> 35:39.304
-♪ Am I ready? ♪

35:39.304 --> 35:42.265
You would think
that attacking a police officer

35:42.265 --> 35:43.975
in front of a bunch of witnesses

35:43.975 --> 35:47.604
at a restaurant would be enough
to put Teddy Lobo behind bars.

35:47.604 --> 35:50.565
You guys don't think I know
what's going on here, huh?

35:50.565 --> 35:52.150
I don't know
how many of you assholes

35:52.150 --> 35:53.651
are on the Lobos' payroll,

35:53.651 --> 35:55.820
but there's only so much
evidence you can tamper with

35:55.820 --> 35:57.822
and so many witnesses
you can intimidate.

35:57.822 --> 35:59.366
All right? Because eventually,

35:59.366 --> 36:01.576
someone brave enough
is going to step forward,

36:01.576 --> 36:03.995
and they're going to help me
take down the Lobos

36:03.995 --> 36:05.872
and all of you motherfuckers!

36:05.872 --> 36:07.999
Permanently! Permanently!

36:11.795 --> 36:13.254
Mr. Renfield?

36:13.254 --> 36:18.676
Robert Montague Renfield,
yes, at your service.

36:18.676 --> 36:21.221
You look different.

36:21.221 --> 36:23.264
-Oh.
-Good different.

36:23.264 --> 36:24.849
I really like your sweater.

36:24.849 --> 36:26.267
Oh, thank you.

36:26.267 --> 36:28.436
-I went to Macy's.
-Oh.

36:28.436 --> 36:30.855
Um, I'm here to give
my witness statement.

36:30.855 --> 36:33.316
You always bring flowers
to give a witness statement?

36:34.609 --> 36:37.404
Yeah, uh, well,
th-they're for everyone.

36:37.404 --> 36:39.531
-They're for everyone.
-Everyone.

36:39.531 --> 36:42.450
Do you, um...
Probably put it in some water.

36:43.243 --> 36:45.870
And the rest are for you.

36:45.870 --> 36:48.206
-Thank you.
-Yeah. Pleasure.

36:48.206 --> 36:50.041
Rebecca, is this your boyfriend?

36:50.041 --> 36:52.335
Shut the fuck up, Kyle!

36:52.335 --> 36:55.213
Thank you for coming in,
Mr. Renfield.

36:56.047 --> 36:58.007
It really means a lot.

36:58.925 --> 37:02.178
Yeah, it means a lot
that I can actually

37:02.178 --> 37:04.722
do the right thing, for once.

37:04.722 --> 37:08.726
Well, if I could just stress
how appreciative I am

37:08.726 --> 37:13.189
that you're here, uh,
because without you,

37:13.189 --> 37:14.983
-I think I'd be a bit lost.
-No.

37:14.983 --> 37:18.653
You stood up for everyone
who's ever lived in fear

37:18.653 --> 37:21.823
of the powerful forces
shaping their lives.

37:21.823 --> 37:24.409
Okay? And you need
to keep doing that,

37:24.409 --> 37:26.911
because when
people like you stop

37:26.911 --> 37:29.622
standing up to people like them,

37:29.622 --> 37:31.916
that's when
the monsters take over.

37:32.876 --> 37:35.378
So...

37:36.963 --> 37:38.882
You are not lost.

37:40.091 --> 37:42.802
You're an inspiration.

37:42.802 --> 37:45.638
Thank you, Mr. Renfield.

37:45.638 --> 37:47.223
It's Robert.

37:47.223 --> 37:49.184
Robert.

37:49.184 --> 37:51.394
This is the same prick

37:51.394 --> 37:53.980
who took out everyone
in the restaurant.

37:53.980 --> 37:55.607
Who does he work for?

37:55.607 --> 37:58.276
-The five fucking families?
-I-I don't know.

37:58.276 --> 38:00.236
But we've hacked into
the NSA's Eye in the Sky,

38:00.236 --> 38:01.779
and we can track him

38:01.779 --> 38:03.448
using all these other cameras
throughout the city.

38:03.448 --> 38:05.074
Yes, I can get you access
to whatever you want.

38:05.074 --> 38:06.618
Yeah, and then we enhance.

38:06.618 --> 38:08.328
-We got a trace on him.
-Boom!

38:08.328 --> 38:10.747
We did it.
Now we can track his every move.

38:11.748 --> 38:14.292
His last known location
is at the old charity hospital.

38:14.292 --> 38:17.003
You have until the end of the
day to find him and kill him.

38:17.003 --> 38:19.297
Give me ten minutes.

38:20.256 --> 38:21.633
I'll take the end of the day.

38:22.967 --> 38:25.929
Can you run the DNA on this pen
through the Bureau's database?

38:25.929 --> 38:27.555
And Interpol.

38:27.555 --> 38:31.017
I can't trust this with anyone
who works in my department.

38:32.560 --> 38:34.354
This pen was found
near a location

38:34.354 --> 38:37.023
where these three guys
went missing.

38:37.023 --> 38:39.400
Teddy Lobo was fleeing
from the same location

38:39.400 --> 38:40.985
when I arrested him.

38:40.985 --> 38:42.320
Huh.

38:42.320 --> 38:44.989
Word on the street is
these are the three guys

38:44.989 --> 38:47.825
who allegedly stole drugs
from the Lobos.

38:47.825 --> 38:48.701
Right.

38:48.701 --> 38:50.912
And the DNA evidence on this pen

38:50.912 --> 38:54.791
just might connect Teddy Lobo
to that crime scene.

38:54.791 --> 38:57.961
Maybe it's a long shot,
but I got to try.

38:59.462 --> 39:04.008
Look, I know I-I haven't
handled anything well

39:04.008 --> 39:07.387
since Dad, um...

39:07.387 --> 39:09.806
but I really need your help.

39:11.182 --> 39:13.059
Can you run this pen?

39:13.059 --> 39:15.019
Please.

39:34.872 --> 39:36.666
Let's go. Come on.

39:58.062 --> 40:00.398
What the fuck?

40:30.178 --> 40:34.015
Holy fucking shit.

40:34.015 --> 40:35.933
Ronnie, call my mom!

40:35.933 --> 40:37.018
I'm on it.

40:37.018 --> 40:39.103
Ronnie, call my fucking mom!

40:44.192 --> 40:45.902
Hello, Ronnie?

40:47.403 --> 40:49.614
Ronnie, is this
another butt dial?

40:49.614 --> 40:52.283
Did you guys fucking bail?
Hello?

40:52.283 --> 40:54.285
-Guys?
-Teddy.

40:54.285 --> 40:56.287
-What the fuck? Mom.
-Teddy.

40:56.287 --> 40:57.789
Mom?

40:58.748 --> 40:59.832
Teddy?

40:59.832 --> 41:01.292
Do you know who the fuck I am?

41:01.292 --> 41:03.878
-Teddy?
-I'm Teddy fucking Lobo.

41:05.296 --> 41:07.965
-I am Count Dracula.

41:07.965 --> 41:09.008
You win.

41:10.385 --> 41:11.803
Who are you?

41:13.388 --> 41:14.972
You were sent by the church?

41:14.972 --> 41:16.057
Church? No.

41:16.057 --> 41:17.308
What are you fucking
talking about?

41:17.308 --> 41:18.601
I'm a criminal.

41:18.601 --> 41:21.312
My whole organization
is about evil.

41:21.312 --> 41:23.022
Evil. Oh, fuck.

41:24.023 --> 41:25.316
Dude.

41:25.316 --> 41:26.609
Why are you here?

41:26.609 --> 41:27.652
I'm here because
I want to find this guy!

41:27.652 --> 41:28.986
I'm trying to find this guy.

41:28.986 --> 41:31.155
He stuck his nose
in our family business

41:31.155 --> 41:33.074
and killed some of our guys

41:33.074 --> 41:35.076
trying to save
a bunch of innocent people.

41:35.076 --> 41:37.662
So, what is he,
like, your fucking roommate?

41:37.662 --> 41:40.081
He's my servant.

41:40.081 --> 41:42.500
He doesn't seem
to be serving you very well.

41:48.047 --> 41:50.007
You've reached Officer Quincy.

41:50.007 --> 41:52.009
Please state your emergency
at the sound of the beep.

41:52.009 --> 41:53.928
-Uh, hi, Rebecca.

41:53.928 --> 41:56.097
It's not an emergency.
It-it's me, Robert.

41:56.097 --> 41:59.809
What, uh, I was trying
to ask was, um,

41:59.809 --> 42:02.437
maybe you'd like
to get a bite to eat...

42:02.437 --> 42:04.814
Hello, Renfield.

42:04.814 --> 42:06.691
I've been expecting you.

42:06.691 --> 42:08.526
Please, come in.

42:08.526 --> 42:10.236
Close the door.

42:13.531 --> 42:15.533
Shit.

42:16.743 --> 42:20.037
Marvelous attire.

42:20.037 --> 42:21.831
Very colorful.

42:21.831 --> 42:24.834
You look like the sort of boy
who has to fight 'em off.

42:26.753 --> 42:29.964
So, I suppose that's a no

42:29.964 --> 42:33.259
as to you bringing me
my dinner tonight, hmm?

42:33.259 --> 42:34.719
-A no? No.
-No?

42:34.719 --> 42:36.345
No, not a no.

42:36.345 --> 42:38.431
-No, not no?
-Uh, yes.

42:39.557 --> 42:41.434
Big yes to dinner.

42:41.434 --> 42:43.978
Ooh. Um, a feast.
A full feast, Master.

42:43.978 --> 42:45.730
In fact,
I'm so glad you're here.

42:45.730 --> 42:49.400
Um, I was actually, um...
I was on my way to see you.

42:49.400 --> 42:50.902
Oh, you were on your way.

42:50.902 --> 42:54.113
Yes, but I had, um,
too many bodies.

42:54.113 --> 42:56.240
-Oh, you-you have bodies, huh?
-Yeah, too... too many.

42:56.240 --> 42:58.868
Well, uh, so many bodies, um,
that I couldn't carry them all.

42:58.868 --> 43:00.411
-Uh, you should have seen it.
-Mm. Mm-hmm.

43:00.411 --> 43:02.955
The problem is my back
has really been playing up.

43:02.955 --> 43:05.458
Anyway, the-the plan is
to rent a U-Haul, and that way,

43:05.458 --> 43:07.418
-I'll be able to get all
the bodies... -Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

43:07.418 --> 43:10.004
You know what? It's so silly,
but you don't have to worry,

43:10.004 --> 43:13.174
um, and I-I won't bother you
with my-my problems.

43:13.174 --> 43:14.842
No, no.

43:14.842 --> 43:18.763
Please, tell me
all about your problems.

43:18.763 --> 43:23.601
Tell me all about
the gun-wielding criminals

43:23.601 --> 43:25.478
who came after you
for killing their men

43:25.478 --> 43:31.025
because you were protecting
so-called innocent people.

43:31.776 --> 43:33.986
I'm-I'm sorry.

43:33.986 --> 43:36.614
I'm sorry, Master.
I never meant to hurt you.

43:36.614 --> 43:39.283
Hurt me?

43:39.283 --> 43:41.285
Are you actually suggesting

43:41.285 --> 43:45.331
that anything you could do
would hurt...

43:45.331 --> 43:46.958
me?!

43:46.958 --> 43:48.709
No. No, no, no, no, no.
No, Master, I'm sorry.

43:48.709 --> 43:50.127
I didn't mean...
I didn't mean that.

43:50.127 --> 43:51.420
No, no, it's-it's all right.
It's all right.

43:51.420 --> 43:52.755
-Really?
-No, it's... Yeah.

43:52.755 --> 43:54.131
Let me explain
something to you, okay?

43:54.131 --> 43:56.926
-Okay.
-I was wrong about you.

43:56.926 --> 44:00.471
I should've realized
what you were capable of

44:00.471 --> 44:02.849
when you were so eager
to join me.

44:02.849 --> 44:04.684
I-I don't think I was eager.

44:04.684 --> 44:06.060
I think that you caught me
at a low moment

44:06.060 --> 44:07.645
-and you maybe manipulated me,
too. -No, no, no,

44:07.645 --> 44:09.438
-no, no... -And you just
caught me at a low moment

44:09.438 --> 44:11.482
-and used some of your power...
-...no, no, no, no, no, no, no!

44:11.482 --> 44:14.569
I use my power
for a lot of things,

44:14.569 --> 44:16.529
but I didn't need
to use it on you.

44:16.529 --> 44:18.906
You were a lawyer
who wanted to get rich

44:18.906 --> 44:20.950
off a real estate deal.

44:20.950 --> 44:22.827
You're the one who used me!

44:22.827 --> 44:26.831
You used my power
because you're a husk.

44:26.831 --> 44:30.126
An empty void
that nothing can fill.

44:30.126 --> 44:34.839
The only thing that gave your
life any meaning was my power.

44:34.839 --> 44:37.967
The power you used
to bring me victims

44:37.967 --> 44:40.428
while you pretended
to be one yourself.

44:41.637 --> 44:45.182
However,
I'm the real victim here!

44:45.182 --> 44:48.936
I'm the one
you swore to protect!

44:50.313 --> 44:52.356
And you...

44:52.356 --> 44:54.150
abandoned me!

44:55.151 --> 44:56.569
No.

44:56.569 --> 44:58.362
That's not true.

44:58.362 --> 45:01.741
Just like you abandoned

45:01.741 --> 45:05.411
your wife and your daughter.

45:07.747 --> 45:09.498
That's not... I didn't...

45:09.498 --> 45:11.042
I didn't abandon them.

45:11.042 --> 45:14.754
Look into your own eyes,
Renfield.

45:14.754 --> 45:19.091
You're the monster, Renfield,
not me.

45:22.803 --> 45:24.722
It's you.

45:25.514 --> 45:27.850
No. No.

45:27.850 --> 45:31.312
That's enough. That's enough.

45:36.484 --> 45:37.526
What?

45:42.073 --> 45:44.408
I will no longer tolerate abuse.

45:46.285 --> 45:47.745
Stop laughing.

45:47.745 --> 45:49.246
I deserve love.

45:50.247 --> 45:51.666
I deserve happiness.

45:51.666 --> 45:53.960
You deserve only suffering.

45:55.086 --> 45:58.422
Um, oh. I know being undead,
it's a painful existence--

45:58.422 --> 46:00.925
it is-- and I empathize
with your pain.

46:00.925 --> 46:02.551
Oh, please. Illuminate me.

46:02.551 --> 46:03.928
Let me learn from you.

46:03.928 --> 46:07.598
I will find everyone
you have ever loved,

46:07.598 --> 46:09.934
and I will drain them.

46:09.934 --> 46:13.312
-I will reduce this... this...
-S-Studio apartment?

46:13.312 --> 46:16.732
...studio apartment
until it's ash!

46:16.732 --> 46:19.527
Uh... uh...

46:21.529 --> 46:23.322
Affirmations, affirmations.

46:23.322 --> 46:26.867
Uh, I'm enough, and, um,
I deserve some happiness.

46:26.867 --> 46:29.245
There is some other stuff
that I have to say.

46:29.245 --> 46:32.289
Who put these ideas
in your head?

46:38.462 --> 46:40.214
Of course.

46:45.094 --> 46:46.429
What?

46:52.226 --> 46:53.811
Shit.

46:55.521 --> 46:58.691
You think Doug was murdered?

46:58.691 --> 47:01.193
I can't say for sure, but I...

47:01.193 --> 47:04.155
I hope he was fucking murdered.

47:04.155 --> 47:08.284
I hope he was torn to
itty-bitty pieces and then...

47:08.284 --> 47:11.996
I shouldn't be saying that
to a cop, right?

47:11.996 --> 47:14.415
Karla, margaritas are ready!

47:14.415 --> 47:16.584
Caitlyn! Oh, God. This...

47:16.584 --> 47:17.752
Try this.

47:17.752 --> 47:18.878
Are you Caitlyn Berggren?

47:18.878 --> 47:20.504
I can be anybody I want now.

47:20.504 --> 47:22.173
That's right. Yes, you can.

47:22.173 --> 47:25.051
Did you file a missing persons
report for Mitch Flaherty?

47:25.051 --> 47:26.969
-Maybe.
-Are you Caitlyn?

47:26.969 --> 47:28.554
H-How do you two
know each other?

47:28.554 --> 47:31.348
-Um, from this support group
thing. -

47:31.348 --> 47:34.060
Uh, for people addicted
to assholes.

47:35.436 --> 47:37.563
-Assholes Anonymous.

47:37.563 --> 47:40.024
At the Livespring Church.

47:40.024 --> 47:44.195
I realized that
I can identify healthy love.

47:44.195 --> 47:47.448
I just don't think I deserve it.

47:47.448 --> 47:49.658
Um, and that's partially
the shame talking,

47:49.658 --> 47:50.868
but also the rash...

47:50.868 --> 47:52.244
Renfield?

47:52.244 --> 47:54.789
Can I get through
one fucking share, please?

47:54.789 --> 47:56.499
Is, uh... is everyone okay?

47:56.499 --> 47:58.167
-If that's what you want to
call it. -MARK: We're all fine.

47:58.167 --> 48:00.002
-What's going on?
What's going on? -We, uh...

48:00.002 --> 48:01.420
We need to leave. Now.

48:01.420 --> 48:03.255
I mean, where's the rule
that says we have to talk

48:03.255 --> 48:05.049
about our feelings in a gym?
Come on, please.

48:05.049 --> 48:07.343
Up. Up. Let's go somewhere safe
till morning.

48:07.343 --> 48:08.886
Come on, up.
Everybody, move. Come on.

48:08.886 --> 48:10.221
Renfield,
just take a deep breath.

48:10.221 --> 48:12.223
We are all fine. I promise...

48:12.223 --> 48:14.100
Mark, we need to leave now.

48:14.100 --> 48:15.893
-All right...

48:18.437 --> 48:22.650
Hi. Uh, are you here
for the meeting?

48:22.650 --> 48:23.984
Well, come on in.

48:23.984 --> 48:26.445
No! No! No!

48:45.089 --> 48:49.468
You can leave your top hat
and cane by the door.

48:50.469 --> 48:51.929
Renfield.

48:53.681 --> 48:57.143
I'm...

48:57.143 --> 48:59.603
feeling much better.

49:03.274 --> 49:04.650
Don't.

49:04.650 --> 49:08.112
Would you like to introduce
yourself to the group?

49:09.780 --> 49:12.158
I'm the prince of Wallachia.

49:16.996 --> 49:20.332
Some call me the Dark One.

49:21.876 --> 49:24.628
Others, the Lord of Death.

49:29.133 --> 49:33.888
However, to most,

49:33.888 --> 49:37.349
I am known simply as...

49:37.349 --> 49:39.643
-Renfield's boss!

49:51.989 --> 49:55.242
I am Dracula.

49:55.242 --> 49:57.244
Okay.
Obviously, we're dealing with

49:57.244 --> 49:59.330
a little bit more than
just narcissism here.

49:59.330 --> 50:00.748
Master.

50:00.748 --> 50:02.041
Please.

50:02.041 --> 50:04.210
I should never
have forsaken you.

50:10.007 --> 50:13.093
You could've had everything.

50:13.093 --> 50:15.221
I gave you the choice between

50:15.221 --> 50:18.265
the power of a god

50:18.265 --> 50:22.519
and the pathetic desperation
of humanity.

50:24.396 --> 50:26.190
Why?

50:26.190 --> 50:29.526
Why would you choose this?

50:29.526 --> 50:31.570
Because...

50:33.280 --> 50:35.783
...that's what I am.

50:38.577 --> 50:41.080
Master, please.

50:41.080 --> 50:42.790
These are good people.

50:42.790 --> 50:47.336
Good. You've finally brought me
what I've been asking for.

50:48.963 --> 50:50.005
Let's eat.

50:50.005 --> 50:52.758
Please. Please. No.

50:52.758 --> 50:53.884
No!

50:55.886 --> 50:57.554
Please, Dracula!

51:25.416 --> 51:26.417
No.

51:27.918 --> 51:31.130
Oh, no, no, no, no. I'm sorry.

51:33.882 --> 51:37.761
There are some experiences

51:37.761 --> 51:40.472
worse than death, Renfield.

51:42.599 --> 51:45.936
Such as spending
the remaining years

51:45.936 --> 51:49.106
of your miserable life

51:49.106 --> 51:52.067
knowing all the depravity

51:52.067 --> 51:54.403
you've witnessed
in the last century

51:54.403 --> 51:58.615
will be nothing
compared to the suffering

51:58.615 --> 52:02.619
I'm going to unleash
on this world.

52:03.454 --> 52:06.457
The world you chose over mine.

52:08.250 --> 52:11.420
When I'm finished,
the entire human race,

52:11.420 --> 52:15.132
everyone you care about,
will suffer.

52:16.967 --> 52:19.470
Because you betrayed me.

52:43.035 --> 52:45.579
-Holy shit.
-Hands in the air.

52:52.378 --> 52:55.798
I destroyed everything.

52:56.799 --> 52:58.342
I'll call it in.

52:58.342 --> 53:01.178
I thought
I could save these people

53:01.178 --> 53:04.181
by bringing Dracula
all of their monsters,

53:04.181 --> 53:05.766
but what I've really done is

53:05.766 --> 53:08.811
deliver my monster
right to them.

53:11.271 --> 53:12.940
Did you call it in?

53:12.940 --> 53:14.733
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

53:38.173 --> 53:39.508
What the fuck?

53:43.011 --> 53:44.888
I'm sorry, Rebecca.

53:54.440 --> 53:56.191
It's okay.

53:56.191 --> 53:58.402
This is not about you,
Miss Quincy.

53:58.402 --> 54:00.821
It's about him.

54:00.821 --> 54:03.657
I need to find out
what happened to Teddy

54:03.657 --> 54:05.993
and punish those responsible.

54:05.993 --> 54:08.537
You, of all people,
should understand that.

54:09.371 --> 54:11.457
Well, I was gonna
take him to jail.

54:11.457 --> 54:12.916
You all should come, too.

54:12.916 --> 54:15.544
Look, Quincy,
this is a big arrest you made.

